# Test Execution Timeouts

Do not abort or kill unit test executions prematurely. Unit tests in this project take a significant amount of time to run.

When running tests via the Shell tool (e.g., `mvn test`, `npm test`):
- Set `block_until_ms` to a sufficiently high value (e.g., `300000` for 5 minutes) or set it to `0` to run in the background.
- Wait patiently for the test process to complete.
- Do not kill the test process just because it appears to be taking a long time.
- Use repeated polling if the process is backgrounded, allowing ample time between checks.
